commit a3f5ed5ffd0a3626566a1b9cc77804f1424fef1c
Author: Patrick Roy <patrick.roy@linux.dev>

KVM: selftests: Test guest execution from direct map removed gmem

This commit adds a selftest that loads itself into guest_memfd and triggers
an MMIO exit when executed. It exercises x86 MMIO emulation code inside
KVM for guest_memfd-backed memslots where the folios are direct map removed.

> diff --git a/tools/testing/selftests/kvm/set_memory_region_test.c b/tools/testing/selftests/kvm/set_memory_region_test.c
> index 7fe427ff9b38..cb445d420e8c 100644
> --- a/tools/testing/selftests/kvm/set_memory_region_test.c
> +++ b/tools/testing/selftests/kvm/set_memory_region_test.c

[ ... ]

> +static void guest_code_trigger_mmio(void)
> +{
> +	/*
> +	 * Read some GPA that is not backed by a memslot. KVM consider this
> +	 * as MMIO and tell userspace to emulate the read.
> +	 */
> +	READ_ONCE(*((uint64_t *)MEM_REGION_GPA));
> +
> +	GUEST_DONE();
> +}
> +
> +static void test_guest_memfd_mmio(void)
> +{
> +	struct kvm_vm *vm;
> +	struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu;
> +	struct vm_shape shape = {
> +		.mode = VM_MODE_DEFAULT,
> +		.src_type = VM_MEM_SRC_GUEST_MEMFD_NO_DIRECT_MAP,
> +	};
> +	pthread_t vcpu_thread;
> +
> +	pr_info("Testing MMIO emulation for instructions in gmem\n");
> +
> +	vm = __vm_create_shape_with_one_vcpu(shape, &vcpu, 0, guest_code_trigger_mmio);
> +
> +	virt_map(vm, MEM_REGION_GPA, MEM_REGION_GPA, 1);
> +
> +	pthread_create(&vcpu_thread, NULL, vcpu_worker, vcpu);
> +
> +	/* If the MMIO read was successfully emulated, the vcpu thread will exit */
> +	pthread_join(vcpu_thread, NULL);

Does this test correctly catch KVM emulation failures?

If KVM encounters a failure during MMIO emulation and returns an
unexpected exit reason like KVM_EXIT_INTERNAL_ERROR, the vcpu_worker
thread loop will simply break and exit without triggering a test failure.

Since there are no assertions on the vCPU's final state or exit reason
after pthread_join() returns, the test will silently pass even if the
x86 MMIO emulation code fails to correctly access gmem.

Could an assertion be added here to verify the final ucall or exit
reason of the vCPU?

> +
> +	kvm_vm_free(vm);
> +}
>  #endif

